<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="997" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1059,481,587]" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">
D i a g n o s i s: The genus 
<emphasis box="[473,564,481,502]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">Ampleris</emphasis>
OPITZ and its 7 previously described species were made available in 2016 (
<bibRefCitation author="OPITZ W" box="[473,599,509,531]" pageId="38" pageNumber="997" pagination="260 - 283" refId="ref53690" refString="OPITZ W. (2016): Taxonomy of the New World Pseudichnea complex (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Peloniinae). - Canadian Entomologist 148: 260 - 283." type="journal article" year="2016">OPITZ 2016</bibRefCitation>
). That work included a key to species. The available 
<emphasis box="[253,434,537,559]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">Ampleris amazon</emphasis>
specimen keys out to 
<emphasis box="[681,775,537,559]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">A. orosis</emphasis>
OPITZ, from which the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">A. amazon</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[236,325,565,587]" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">holotype</typeStatus>
differs by showing a more rounded pronotal tubercle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="997" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1059,601,903]" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 
<quantity box="[516,597,601,623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="38" pageNumber="997" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity box="[673,753,601,622]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="38" pageNumber="997" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[895,980,601,623]" captionStart="Figs 213-218" captionStartId="85.[151,191,1262,1284]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,202,1251]" captionTargetId="figure@85.[153,1061,202,1251]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="Figs 213-218: Aedeagi; (213) Perilypus virgulatus; (214) Agnatis curvabilis; (215) A. vaurieae; (216) Parapelonides naranjo; (217) Pyticara frontegalba; (218) Amboakis bermejo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746776" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746776/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">Fig. 216</figureCitation>
. Color: Clypeus and lower frons testaceous, upper frons and epicranium brown, except epicranium with narrow testaceous streak at middle; gena testaceous; antenna brown; prothorax bicolored, venter testaceous; pronotum bicolored, disc broadly black at sides, with broad testaceous line at middle, testaceous region laden with yellow setae; pterothorax, elytra, legs, and abdomen piceous. Head: Cranium coarsely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation box="[250,331,769,791]" captionStart="Figs 92-100" captionStartId="74.[151,191,872,894]" captionTargetBox="[175,1038,229,838]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[155,1062,203,862]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="Figs 92-100: Antennae; (92) Pyticeroides desodes; (93) Ichnea cerinis; (94) Agnatis vaurieae; (95) Ampleris amazon; (96) Nepsudia guenda; (97) Isoparis cassidilis; (98) Pelonium atrigonatium; (99) Aphelocerus yaguare; (100) Madoniella selvanegra." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746754/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres transverse, very setose, capitular antennomeres narrow oblong; eyes small, coarsely facetted, eye as wide as frons (EW/FW 23/23). Thorax: Pronotal disc (
<figureCitation box="[589,681,825,847]" captionStart="Figs 118-133" captionStartId="76.[151,191,1373,1395]" captionTargetBox="[152,1050,202,1340]" captionTargetId="figure@76.[152,1056,202,1357]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figs 118-133: Pronota; (118) Pujoliclerus abditus; (119) Nelsopelonium aspikelum; (120) Parapelonides naranjo; (121) Pujoliclerus lasiosus; (122) Neorthopleura rubra; (123) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (124) Ichnea cerinis; (125) Ampleris amazon; (126) Pujoliclerus abditus; (127) P. dexsus; (128) Sirpa acara; (129) Madoniella aspera; (130) Pelonium tayrona; (131) Megatrachys irrasis; (132) Ordinis taxis; (133) Pujoliclerus cnecostus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746758" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746758/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="997">Fig. 125</figureCitation>
) coarsely punctate, slightly oblong (PW/PL 70/75); lateral tubercle well developed; elytral asetiferous punctures substriate (EL/EW 240/55). Abdomen: Pygidium subquadrate/scutiform.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
